As shown in the methodology of the problem, the current work investigates the MHD Reiner–Rivlin nanofluid. Accordingly, this mechanism has enhanced the heat transfer rate. Therefore, Figs. 12 and 13 are designed to confirm this imperative phenomenon, where heat distribution rises by the rise of both the magnetic factor M\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
